Ectosomal skeleton a dense, uni- to paucispicular, isotropic reticulation, slightly confused, but with some discernible triangular to squared meshes (
Fig. 9E
). Choanosome of the same structure as the ectosome, albeit there are some subectosomal and choanosomal spaces, 600–1500 µm (
Fig. 9C, D
). Spongin scarce, only observed at the nodes of the reticulation.
